	<heading>Why teach Ruby in schools?</heading>
	
	<p>There are <a href="/education/programming-language-comparison">many languages available</a>... so why teach Ruby?</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Ruby is easy to read and write. It has a simple and consistent syntax.</li>
		<li>Ruby helps you to express your ideas concisely.</li>
		<li>Ruby is a modern language with support for a useful range of modern programming constructs.</li>
		<li>Ruby is free and available for all major platforms.</li>
		<li>Ruby has a great community of people who can help.</li>
		<li>Ruby has many modules and frameworks for doing additional things such as web apps, databases, networking, games, etc..</li>
		<li>Ruby is full of best-practice and creativity.</li>
	</ul>
	
